# Mobile-First Tarmac Application

**Mobile-first webapp** with Symfony + Tabler.io. Prioritize mobile (320px+), enhance for desktop (768px+).

## Core Principles
- **Mobile-first**: Design for mobile screens first, then enhance
- **Touch-optimized**: All interactions work on touch devices
- **Performance-first**: Optimize for mobile networks
- **Use Tabler components**: Leverage Tabler's mobile-optimized UI

## Layout & Components
- Single column layouts on mobile by default
- Card-based designs for readability
- Touch targets: minimum 44px × 44px
- Tables: card layout or horizontal scroll on mobile
- Use responsive classes: `d-block d-md-none`, `d-none d-md-block`

## Forms & Interactions
- Full-width inputs on mobile
- Always visible labels (not placeholder-only)
- Touch-friendly controls with proper spacing
- Progressive enhancement (works without JS)

## Styling
- Extend Tabler in `/assets/styles/app.css`
- Mobile-first media queries: `@media (min-width: 768px)`
- Use Tabler utility classes and spacing scale
- Semantic HTML5 with ARIA labels

## Performance
- First Contentful Paint: < 1.5s on 3G
- Optimize images (WebP format)
- Lazy load non-critical scripts

## JavaScript
- Use Stimulus controllers for interactivity
- Touch-friendly event handlers
- Debounce scroll/resize events

## Key Anti-Patterns to Avoid
- ❌ Desktop-first design
- ❌ Fixed widths that don't scale
- ❌ Tiny touch targets (< 44px)
- ❌ Hover-only interactions

Remember: Mobile first, then enhance for larger screens.